MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0086 cleanly separates Indian and Global views per the user's explicit ask
('SPML / NTPC story should not surface GEV / HTHIY / PRY.MI'):

1. INDIA_ROSTER (39 NSE-listed names across L1-L6)
   L1 capture:  POWERGRID / NTPC / BHEL / COALINDIA / TATAPOWER / ABB.NS /
                SIEMENS.NS / CGPOWER / KAYNES / KECL / ADANIGREEN
   L2 design:   TATAELXSI / LTTS / KPITTECH / PERSISTENT / COFORGE
   L3 edge:     BHARTIARTL / TATACOMM / TEJASNET / CYIENT
   L4 transm.:  STL.NS / HFCL / POLYCAB / KEI / FINCABLES / LINDEINDIA /
                HEG / GRAPHITE / DIXON
   L5 platform: TCS / INFY / RELIANCE / WIPRO / HCLTECH
   L6 thermal:  VOLTAS / BLUESTARCO / HAVELLS / CROMPTON / KIRLOSKARP / THERMAX

2. NODE_RULES_IN — India-specific mandatory injections per SystemNode
   - RENEWABLE_INFRA -> POWERGRID + NTPC + BHEL + ADANIGREEN + cable chain
   - ENERGY_INFRA    -> POWERGRID + NTPC + BHEL + ABB.NS + SIEMENS.NS + KEC + CG
   - INTERCONNECT    -> BHARTIARTL + TATACOMM + TEJASNET + STL/HFCL/POLYCAB

3. inferRegion(sources, titles, tickers) -> 'IN' | 'GLOBAL'
   Detects: Indian publishers (Mint / ET / Power Line / Moneycontrol /
   BSE / NSE / SEBI / RBI / PIB / CNBC TV18), Rs/₹/crore/lakh tokens,
   PSU + city + .NS/.BO ticker suffixes.

4. deriveLayeredBeneficiaries({ ..., region }) — region-scoped roster lookup.
   When region==='IN' uses INDIA_ROSTER + NODE_RULES_IN exclusively.

5. Persistent-bottleneck endpoint splits each item by region:
   For each item we partition top_samples by inferred region. If both
   regions have samples we EMIT TWO ITEMS (one IN, one GLOBAL) each with
   region-scoped layered_beneficiaries + region-scoped top sample.

6. Page renders one panel with two sub-sections via region-divider sentinels:
     🇮🇳 INDIA — N bottlenecks · NSE-listed beneficiaries only
     🌐 GLOBAL — N bottlenecks · global L1-L6 roster

7. Liveness pill in section header.
   Computed from response.last_updated (server-side ISO timestamp).
   Green ≤10min, amber ≤24h, red older. Tooltip shows exact timestamp.
   Query already auto-refreshes every 5 min — pill proves it.

Cache key bumped v31 -> v32.
